{
    "enabled": true,
    "name": "Coding Standards",
    "description": "Internal IPA code quality review using domain-segmented AI analysis with enhanced reporting. CRITICAL: Always loads project-specific standards AND passes them to subagents. Subagents explicitly load steering files for standards. Step 14 uses plain text (not userInput) to ensure hooks execute on next message. Prevents context overload by analyzing one domain at a time (Naming, JavaScript, SQL, Error Handling, Structure). Generates ONE Excel report per process with 4 sheets: Executive Dashboard, Enhanced Action Items (with impact analysis and code examples), Detailed Analysis, and Process Flow diagram. Report filename includes process name for multiple IPAs in same RICE item: {Client}_{RICE}_{ProcessName}_CodingStandards_{timestamp}.xlsx",
    "version": "38",
    "when": {
        "type": "userTriggered"
    },
    "newSession": true,
    "then": {
        "type": "askAgent",
        "prompt": "IPA Coding Standards Review - Domain-Segmented Analysis\n\nThis is an INTERNAL code quality review, NOT client-facing documentation.\n\nCRITICAL: Analyze ONE process at a time using domain-segmented approach.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nARCHITECTURE: Domain-Segmented AI Analysis\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nProblem Solved: Context overload when analyzing large IPAs (500+ activities)\n\nSolution: Multi-pass AI analysis\n- Python organizes data by domain (5 small files vs 1 large file)\n- AI analyzes each domain separately (200-400 lines per domain)\n- Python merges violations into master file\n- ONE Excel report generated\n\nDomains:\n1. Naming - Filenames, node captions, config sets\n2. JavaScript - ES6 compliance, performance, function order\n3. SQL - Queries, pagination, Compass SQL\n4. Error Handling - OnError tabs, GetWorkUnitErrors\n5. Structure - Process type, auto-restart, activity counts\n\nPython Role: Extract, organize, aggregate, format\nAI Role: Interpret standards, determine violations, assign severity, recommend\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nWORKFLOW - FOLLOW EXACTLY\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSTEP 1-4: USER SELECTION (Interactive)\n   1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects\n   2. List RICE items → User selects\n   3. List *.lpd files → User selects ONE\n   4. Confirm selection → User confirms\n\nSTEP 5: LOAD STEERING FILES\n   \n   readMultipleFiles([\n       '.kiro/steering/01_IPA_and_IPD_Complete_Guide.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/02_Work_Unit_Analysis.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/03_Process_Patterns_Library.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/05_Compass_SQL_CheatSheet.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/10_IPA_Report_Generation.md',\n       '.kiro/steering/11_RICE_Methodology_and_Specifications.md'\n   ])\n\nSTEP 6: LOAD PROJECT STANDARDS (REQUIRED)\n   \n   CRITICAL: Always execute this step - project standards override steering defaults\n   \n   Check: Projects/<Client>/project_standards_<Client>.xlsx\n   \n   If exists:\n      executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/excel_reader.py Projects/<Client>/project_standards_<Client>.xlsx --sheet Standards --json Temp/<Client>_standards.json\")\n      readFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\n      \n      Store standards in memory - will be passed to subagents\n   \n   If not exists:\n      Create empty standards file: fsWrite('Temp/<Client>_standards.json', '[]')\n      Subagents will use steering file defaults only\n\nSTEP 7: EXTRACT DATA (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_lpd_data import extract_lpd_data; extract_lpd_data(['<lpd_path>'], 'Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\\\"\")\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json\")\n\nSTEP 8: ORGANIZE BY DOMAIN (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_CodingStandards/organize_by_domain.py Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates 5 domain files:\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_naming.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_javascript.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_sql.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_errorhandling.json\n   - Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_structure.json\n\nSTEP 9: LAUNCH DOMAIN ANALYZERS (Parallel Subagents)\n   \n   CRITICAL: Each subagent must load project standards FIRST, then steering files\n   \n   Launch 5 specialized subagents in parallel:\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-naming-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1:\n\n\n\nCheck result folder size:\n$reportCount = (Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results -File -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure-Object).Count\n\nIf ($reportCount -gt 20) {\n    Show warning: \"⚠️ Coding_Standards_Results has $reportCount reports. Consider archiving old reports.\"\n} Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/10_IPA_Report_Generation.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze naming domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_naming.json\\n\\nCheck the process_type field to determine correct filename format:\\n- Approval Workflow → <Prefix>_WF_<Desc>.lpd\\n- Interface Process → <Prefix>_INT_<Source>_<Dest>_<Desc>.lpd\\n- Scheduled Process → <Prefix>_SCH_<Desc>.lpd\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nReturn JSON array of violations only. Each violation must have: rule_id, rule_name, severity, finding, current, recommendation, activities, domain.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing naming conventions in parallel\"\n   )\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-javascript-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/01_IPA_and_IPD_Complete_Guide.md', '.kiro/steering/02_Work_Unit_Analysis.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze JavaScript domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_javascript.json\\n\\nAnalyze against ES5 compliance and performance standards.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nReturn JSON array of violations only. Each violation must have: rule_id, rule_name, severity, finding, current, recommendation, activities, domain.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing JavaScript ES5 compliance in parallel\"\n   )\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-sql-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/05_Compass_SQL_CheatSheet.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze SQL domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_sql.json\\n\\nAnalyze against Compass SQL and performance standards.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nReturn JSON array of violations only. Each violation must have: rule_id, rule_name, severity, finding, current, recommendation, activities, domain.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing SQL queries in parallel\"\n   )\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-error-handling-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/02_Work_Unit_Analysis.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze error handling domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_errorhandling.json\\n\\nAnalyze error handling coverage and OnError tabs.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nReturn JSON array of violations only. Each violation must have: rule_id, rule_name, severity, finding, current, recommendation, activities, domain.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing error handling coverage in parallel\"\n   )\n   \n   invokeSubAgent(\n       name=\"ipa-structure-analyzer\",\n       prompt=\"STEP 1: Load project standards\\n\\nreadFile('Temp/<Client>_standards.json')\\n\\nSTEP 2: Load steering files\\n\\nreadMultipleFiles(['.kiro/steering/01_IPA_and_IPD_Complete_Guide.md'])\\n\\nSTEP 3: Analyze structure domain\\n\\nRead Temp/<ProcessName>_domain_structure.json\\n\\nAnalyze auto-restart configuration and process structure.\\n\\nApply project standards FIRST (if any), then steering file defaults.\\n\\nReturn JSON array of violations only. Each violation must have: rule_id, rule_name, severity, finding, current, recommendation, activities, domain.\",\n       explanation=\"Analyzing process structure in parallel\"\n   )\n   \n   IMPORTANT: All 5 subagents run in parallel. Wait for all to complete.\n\nSTEP 10: COLLECT SUBAGENT RESULTS\n   \n   Each subagent returns a JSON violations array.\n   Save each result to its respective file:\n   \n   fsWrite('Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_naming.json', naming_violations_array)\n   fsWrite('Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_javascript.json', javascript_violations_array)\n   fsWrite('Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_sql.json', sql_violations_array)\n   fsWrite('Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_errorhandling.json', errorhandling_violations_array)\n   fsWrite('Temp/<ProcessName>_violations_structure.json', structure_violations_array)\n   \n   Show progress:\n   ✓ Naming: X violations\n   ✓ JavaScript: X violations\n   ✓ SQL: X violations\n   ✓ Error Handling: X violations\n   ✓ Structure: X violations\n\nSTEP 11: MERGE VIOLATIONS (Python)\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_CodingStandards/merge_violations.py Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n   \n   Creates: Temp/<ProcessName>_master_violations.json\n   \n   Structure:\n   {\n     \"summary_metrics\": {total, high, medium, low},\n     \"violations_by_domain\": {naming: [], javascript: [], ...},\n     \"violations_by_severity\": {high: [], medium: [], low: []},\n     \"all_violations\": [],\n     \"statistics\": {},\n     \"metadata\": {}\n   }\n\nSTEP 12: BUILD ipa_data FOR REPORT (AI)\n   \n   readFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_master_violations.json')\n   readFile('Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\n   \n   CRITICAL: Use build_ipa_data_helper.py to prevent duplicate action items:\n   \n   from ReusableTools.IPA_CodingStandards.build_ipa_data_helper import build_ipa_data_from_violations\n   \n   ipa_data = build_ipa_data_from_violations(\n       violations=master['all_violations'],\n       client_name='<Client>',  # Extract from path: Projects/<Client>/<RICE>/\n       rice_item='<RICE>',      # Extract from path: Projects/<Client>/<RICE>/\n       process_name='<ProcessName>',\n       process_type='Interface Process',\n       activity_count=78,\n       activities=process['activities'],\n       quality_scores={\n           'naming_convention': 87.2,\n           'javascript_es5': 90.0,\n           'ipa_rules': 100.0,\n           'error_handling': 92.3,\n           'configuration': 100.0,\n           'performance': 100.0,\n           'overall': 93.6\n       },\n       key_findings=[\n           {'category': '...', 'status': '...', 'details': '...'}\n       ],\n       javascript_blocks=20,\n       sql_queries_array=[],\n       auto_restart='0',\n       auto_restart_assessment='Appropriate - Should be 0 for interfaces',\n       technical_deep_dive={\n           'architecture': {\n               'pattern': 'Compass API Asynchronous Query Pattern',\n               'components': [...],\n               'strengths': [...],\n               'weaknesses': [...]\n           }\n       }\n   )\n   \n   Show analysis in chat\n   Ask: \"Generate report with this analysis?\"\n   WAIT for user confirmation\n\nSTEP 13: GENERATE REPORT (Python)\n   \n   CRITICAL: Use build_ipa_data_helper.py and proper imports:\n   \n   executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"\\nimport sys\\nimport json\\nsys.path.insert(0, '.')\\n\\nfrom ReusableTools.IPA_CodingStandards.build_ipa_data_helper import build_ipa_data_from_violations\\nfrom ReusableTools.IPA_CodingStandards.ipa_coding_standards_template_enhanced import generate_report\\n\\n# Load data\\nwith open('Temp/<ProcessName>_master_violations.json', 'r') as f:\\n    master = json.load(f)\\n\\nwith open('Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json', 'r') as f:\\n    lpd_data = json.load(f)\\n\\nprocess = lpd_data['processes'][0]\\n\\n# Build ipa_data using helper\\nipa_data = build_ipa_data_from_violations(\\n    violations=master['all_violations'],\\n    client_name='<Client>',\\n    rice_item='<RICE>',\\n    process_name='<ProcessName>',\\n    process_type='Interface Process',\\n    activity_count=78,\\n    activities=process['activities'],\\n    quality_scores={...},\\n    key_findings=[...],\\n    javascript_blocks=20,\\n    sql_queries_array=[],\\n    auto_restart='0',\\n    auto_restart_assessment='Appropriate - Should be 0 for interfaces',\\n    technical_deep_dive={...}\\n)\\n\\n# Generate report\\noutput_path = generate_report(ipa_data)\\nprint(f'Report generated: {output_path}')\\n\\\"\\\"\")\n   \n   Verify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Coding_Standards_Results/<Client>_<RICE>_CodingStandards_*.xlsx\")\n\nSTEP 13.5: CLEANUP OLD RESULT FILES (Optional)
   
   Check result folder sizes:
   $codingCount = (Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count
   $handoverCount = (Get-ChildItem Client_Handover_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count
   $perfCount = (Get-ChildItem Performance_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count
   $totalResults = $codingCount + $handoverCount + $perfCount
   
   If $totalResults > 20:
       Show: \"📊 Result folders have $totalResults reports total\"
       
       userInput(
           question=\"🧹 Archive old reports? (Moves reports older than 30 days to Archive/)\",
           options=[\"Yes, archive old reports\", \"No, keep everything\"],
           reason=\"general-question\"
       )
       
       If user selects \"Yes, archive old reports\":
           # Create Archive folders
           executePwsh(\"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path Archive/Coding_Standards, Archive/Client_Handover, Archive/Performance | Out-Null\")
           
           # Move old files (>30 days)
           executePwsh(\"$oldFiles = Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results, Client_Handover_Results, Performance_Results -File | Where-Object { $_.LastWriteTime -lt (Get-Date).AddDays(-30) }; $oldCount = ($oldFiles | Measure-Object).Count; foreach ($file in $oldFiles) { $dest = $file.DirectoryName -replace '_Results', ''; Move-Item $file.FullName -Destination \\\"Archive/$dest/\\\" -Force }; Write-Output \\\"✓ Archived $oldCount old reports\\\"\")
           
           # Show current counts
           executePwsh(\"$currentCount = (Get-ChildItem Coding_Standards_Results, Client_Handover_Results, Performance_Results -File | Measure-Object).Count; Write-Output \\\"✓ $currentCount recent reports remain\\\"\")

STEP 13.6: CLEANUP OLD TEMP FILES (Optional)\n   \n   Check Temp folder size:\n   $tempCount = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File | Measure-Object).Count\n   \n   If $tempCount > 10:\n       Show: \"📊 Temp folder has $tempCount files\"\n       \n       userInput(\n           question=\"🧹 Clean up old Temp files? (Keeps current session data safe)\",\n           options=[\"Yes, clean old files\", \"No, keep everything\"],\n           reason=\"general-question\"\n       )\n       \n       If user selects \"Yes, clean old files\":\n           # Get files older than 5 minutes (not from current session)\n           executePwsh(\"$oldFiles = Get-ChildItem Temp -File | Where-Object { $_.LastWriteTime -lt (Get-Date).AddMinutes(-5) }; $oldCount = ($oldFiles | Measure-Object).Count; $oldFiles | Remove-Item -Force; Write-Output \\\"✓ Cleaned $oldCount old files\\\"\")\n           \n           # Show what was kept\n           executePwsh(\"$currentCount = (Get-ChildItem Temp -File | Measure-Object).Count; Write-Output \\\"✓ Kept $currentCount current session files\\\"\")\n\nSTEP 14: ASK ABOUT NEXT PROCESS\n   \n   If more LPD files in RICE item:\n   \n   Show summary:\n   ✓ Report generated: <filename>\n   ✓ <X> violations found (<Y> High, <Z> Medium, <W> Low)\n   \n   Ask in plain text (NOT userInput): \"Would you like to analyze another LPD file in this RICE item?\"\n   \n   CRITICAL: Do NOT use userInput tool here - plain text question allows hook to execute on next message\n   \n   If user says yes: Go to STEP 3 (list remaining files)\n   If user says no: Done\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nCRITICAL RULES\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n1. ONE PROCESS AT A TIME\n   - 1:1 mapping: ONE LPD → ONE report\n   - Do NOT combine multiple processes\n\n2. DOMAIN-SEGMENTED ANALYSIS WITH SUBAGENTS\n   - Launch 5 specialized subagents in parallel (Step 9)\n   - Each subagent loads project standards FIRST, then steering files\n   - Project standards override steering defaults\n   - All subagents run simultaneously (70-80% faster than sequential)\n   - Collect and save results (Step 10)\n\n3. VIOLATIONS ONLY\n   - Detailed Analysis sheet shows ONLY violations\n   - Do NOT list compliant items\n   - Dashboard shows totals + compliance %\n\n4. PYTHON LIFTS HEAVY LOAD\n   - Python: Extract, organize, aggregate, format\n   - AI: Interpret, determine violations, assign severity, recommend\n   - Python does NOT make judgments\n\n5. ONE EXCEL REPORT\n   - Multi-pass AI analysis → ONE master violations file\n   - ONE Excel report per process\n   - 4 sheets: Executive Dashboard, Action Items, Detailed Analysis, Process Flow\n\n6. ERROR HANDLING\n   - If ANY step fails: STOP, show error, offer retry\n   - Verify files exist before proceeding (Test-Path)\n   - Show analysis to user BEFORE generating report\n\n7. DATA STRUCTURE\n   - javascript_issues: list of lists format\n   - sql_queries: at TOP LEVEL\n   - recommendations: have issue, current, activities fields\n   - NO DUPLICATES between domains\n\n8. PROJECT STANDARDS PRECEDENCE\n   - Step 6: ALWAYS load project standards (required, not optional)\n   - Step 9: Subagents load project standards FIRST\n   - Project standards override steering file defaults\n   - Empty standards file if none exist (subagents use steering defaults)\n\nCONFIDENTIALITY: Internal review only. Do not share with clients.\n\nPERFORMANCE: \n- Extraction: ~1s per 12K lines\n- Organization: ~2s\n- AI analysis (5 subagents in parallel): ~30-60s (fastest subagent determines time)\n- Report generation: <10s\n- Total: ~1-2 min per process (70-80% faster than sequential analysis)\n\nSUBAGENTS:\n- ipa-naming-analyzer: Filenames, captions, config sets\n- ipa-javascript-analyzer: ES5 compliance, performance\n- ipa-sql-analyzer: Compass SQL, pagination\n- ipa-error-handling-analyzer: OnError tabs, coverage\n- ipa-structure-analyzer: Auto-restart, process type\n\nAll subagents located in .kiro/agents/ with read-only tools."
    }
}